### ============================================================
### HR Salary System — HTTP Client request stubs
### ============================================================
### Usage in WebStorm:
###   1. Copy http-client.env.json.example → http-client.env.json
###   2. Fill in token (or hit "Login" first — script writes it)
###   3. Choose env: "dev" / "prod" at top right
###   4. Click ▶ next to any request
###
### Pipeline reference (CLAUDE.md Section 3, 7 stages):
###   1 import  →  2 miss-punch  →  3 shift-check  →  4 night-shift
###   →  5 corrections  →  6 day-calc  →  7 salary-compute
### ============================================================


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Health (public, no auth)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health
Accept: application/json


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Auth — Login (writes hr_token + sets {{token}})
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("token", response.body.token);
  client.log("token captured for subsequent requests");
%}


### Auth — Current user
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Auth — Heartbeat (keeps session alive)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/heartbeat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Auth — Permission matrix
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Employees (CRUD)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Employees — List (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/employees?company=Indriyan Beverages&status=Active&limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Employees — Get one by code
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/employees/{{employeeCode}}?company=Indriyan Beverages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Employees — Create
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/employees
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "REPLACE_ME",
  "name": "Test Employee",
  "department": "QA",
  "company": "Indriyan Beverages",
  "designation": "Operator",
  "date_of_joining": "2026-05-01",
  "gross_salary": 18000,
  "is_contractor": 0
}


### Employees — Update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/employees/{{employeeCode}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "department": "QA",
  "designation": "Senior Operator"
}


### Employees — Mark left (soft delete; respects manual marker)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/employees/{{employeeCode}}/mark-left
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "exit_date": "2026-05-31",
  "exit_reason": "Resigned"
}


### Employees — Update salary (gated by finance approval if gross changes)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/employees/{{employeeCode}}/salary
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "gross_salary": 22000,
  "basic": 13200,
  "hra": 5280,
  "conveyance": 1600,
  "other_allowances": 1920,
  "remark": "Annual hike"
}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Biometric attendance upload (Stage 1)
### Use WebStorm's "+" → file in the body — DON'T paste binary in here
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/import/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----HR-IMPORT-BOUNDARY

------HR-IMPORT-BOUNDARY
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="month"

{{month}}
------HR-IMPORT-BOUNDARY
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="year"

{{year}}
------HR-IMPORT-BOUNDARY
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="company"

Indriyan Beverages
------HR-IMPORT-BOUNDARY
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="EESL_apr_2026.xls"
Content-Type: application/vnd.ms-excel

< ./samples/EESL_apr_2026.xls
------HR-IMPORT-BOUNDARY--


### Import — History
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/import/history?month={{month}}&year={{year}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Import — Summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/import/summary/{{month}}/{{year}}?company=Indriyan Beverages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Stage transitions — Attendance (Stages 2-5)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Stage 2 — List unresolved miss punches
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/miss-punches?month={{month}}&year={{year}}&company=Indriyan Beverages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Stage 2 — Resolve a miss punch
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/miss-punches/{{missPunchId}}/resolve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "in_time_final": "08:30",
  "out_time_final": "18:30",
  "status_final": "P",
  "remark": "Forgot to punch OUT"
}


### Stage 4 — Night shift pairs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/night-shifts?month={{month}}&year={{year}}&company=Indriyan Beverages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Stage 4 — Confirm pair
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/night-shifts/{{pairId}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Stage 5 — Recalculate metrics (after shift/punch corrections)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/recalculate-metrics
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "month": {{month}},
  "year": {{year}},
  "company": "Indriyan Beverages"
}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Stage transitions — Payroll (Stages 6-7)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Stage 6 — Calculate days
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payroll/calculate-days
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "month": {{month}},
  "year": {{year}},
  "company": "Indriyan Beverages"
}


### Stage 6 — Day calc register
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/payroll/day-calculations?month={{month}}&year={{year}}&company=Indriyan Beverages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Stage 7 — Compute salary
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payroll/compute-salary
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "month": {{month}},
  "year": {{year}},
  "company": "Indriyan Beverages"
}


### Stage 7 — Salary register
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/payroll/salary-register?month={{month}}&year={{year}}&company=Indriyan Beverages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Stage 7 — Finalise (gated by finance signoff)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payroll/finalise
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "month": {{month}},
  "year": {{year}},
  "company": "Indriyan Beverages"
}


### Stage 7 — Payslip JSON for one employee
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/payroll/payslip/{{employeeCode}}?month={{month}}&year={{year}}&company=Indriyan Beverages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Reports / Exports
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Bank NEFT CSV
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reports/bank-salary-file?month={{month}}&year={{year}}&company=Indriyan Beverages&download=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### PF ECR
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reports/pf-ecr?month={{month}}&year={{year}}&company=Indriyan Beverages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ESI return
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reports/esi-return?month={{month}}&year={{year}}&company=Indriyan Beverages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Finance verification — sign-off (gates Stage 7 finalise)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Finance — Red flags
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/finance-verify/red-flags?month={{month}}&year={{year}}&company=Indriyan Beverages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Finance — Sign off month
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/finance-verify/signoff
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "month": {{month}},
  "year": {{year}},
  "company": "Indriyan Beverages",
  "status": "approved",
  "remark": "All red flags reviewed"
}
